items.title: Awesome Clojure Updates on Oct 31, 2021
items.content_text:
### Awesome macros usage

*   [core.async (⭐2k)](https://github.com/clojure/core.async) - transforms AST into CSP programs
*   [cloroutine (⭐236)](https://github.com/leonoel/cloroutine) - suspends and continuations (coroutines)
*   [missionary (⭐740)](https://github.com/leonoel/missionary) - a reactive dataflow programming toolkit
*   [photon (⭐7)](https://github.com/venantius/photon) - realtime web, like Meteor, but for Clojure(Script)
*   [metaclj (⭐81)](https://github.com/brandonbloom/metaclj) - staged compilation
*   [proteus (⭐113)](https://github.com/ztellman/proteus) - introduce mutable variables (don't use, just learn how to map your mind into immutable world)
items.content_html:
Awesome macros usage

  • core.async (⭐2k) - transforms AST into CSP programs
  • cloroutine (⭐236) - suspends and continuations (coroutines)
  • missionary (⭐740) - a reactive dataflow programming toolkit
  • photon (⭐7) - realtime web, like Meteor, but for Clojure(Script)
  • metaclj (⭐81) - staged compilation
  • proteus (⭐113) - introduce mutable variables (don't use, just learn how to map your mind into immutable world)

items.title: Awesome Clojure Updates on Nov 05, 2018
items.content_text:
### Advanced datastructures

*   [Persistent AVL trees (⭐133)](https://github.com/clojure/data.avl): persistent sorted maps and sets with log-time rank queries
*   [Finger Tree (⭐216)](https://github.com/clojure/data.finger-tree): double-list, counted-double-list, counted-sorted-set
*   [Hitchhiker Tree (⭐1.2k)](https://github.com/datacrypt-project/hitchhiker-tree): create fast, snapshottable, massively scalable databases
*   [Hierarchical set (⭐8)](https://github.com/llasram/hier-set)
*   [Ordered (⭐263)](https://github.com/amalloy/ordered): ordered sets and maps
*   [Lazy Map (⭐49)](https://github.com/Malabarba/lazy-map-clojure): whose values are only calculated when accessed
*   [Durable Queue (⭐389)](https://github.com/Factual/durable-queue): queue persisted on disk
*   [bifurcan (⭐999)](https://github.com/lacuna/bifurcan): linear map/set/list (stores entries contiguously in memory), ;writtern in java, but test suite (read: usage examples) [in clojure (⭐999)](https://github.com/lacuna/bifurcan/blob/master/test/bifurcan)
items.content_html:
